# Code Quality Rules (agent-code-constraints.md)

## Hard Limits
| Metric | Hard limit | Preferred |
|--------|-----------|-----------|
| Function length | 50 lines | ≤ 30 |
| Parameters | 5 | ≤ 3 |
| Nesting depth | 3 | ≤ 2 |
| File length | 300 lines | ≤ 200 |
| Cyclomatic complexity | 10 | ≤ 5 |

## Patterns

### Early return (flatten nesting)
```ts
// ❌ deep nesting
if (order) {
  if (order.items.length > 0) {
    order.items.forEach(item => {
      if (item.inStock) { fulfillItem(item); }
    });
  }
}

// ✅ early return
if (!order || order.items.length === 0) return;
order.items.filter(i => i.inStock).forEach(fulfillItem);
```

### Options object (> 3 params)
```ts
// ❌ too many params
function createUser(name, email, role, orgId, sendWelcome) {}

// ✅ options object
function createUser(options: { name: string; email: string; role: Role; orgId: string; sendWelcome?: boolean }) {}
```

## Comments
Only when WHY is non-obvious. Never explain WHAT the code does.
